Information
------------------------------

Big Dreams Small Spaces: Series 2
Monty Don returns to help more amateur horticulturists transform their small or average-sized plots into something extraordinary.


3)  Bromley 
Monty helps Bromley couple Mei and Gerard with their ambitious plan to turn their narrow, split-level garden into a Japanese-style paradise, complete with mountain stream, mossy boulders and traditional plants. But with tons of soil to move and their budget running out, it seems they have bitten off more than they can chew. In Stoke, artists Anna and Andrew want to transform their concrete yard into a haven of tranquillity with something beautiful to see in every corner. However, they will need to use all their creative flair - not to mention Monty's expert advice - to avoid overcrowding this very small space.
